cdebconf-entropy (0.9) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  [ Jérémy Bobbio ]
  * In the GTK+ plugin, all random bytes available are now moved in the same
    row before refreshing the interface.
  * In the GTK+ plugin, allow_continue() now properly handle GDK threads.
    This prevent race issues in the display of the success message.
  * Fix minor usability issues in the GTK+ plugin:            (Closes: #479325)
    - Display the help text in a similar way than normal extended
      descriptions.
    - Display a completion percentage while gathering entropy.
    - Disallow entering more character once enough entropy has been gathered.
    - Reset text entry after gathering more entropy.
  * In the GTK+ plugin, the cleanup function is now also called when the
    "Go back" is activated.

 -- Jérémy Bobbio <lunar@debian.org>  Thu, 08 May 2008 13:37:50 +0000

